---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import MainHead from "../../components/MainHead.astro";
import Nav from "../../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

import FlyAirwaysImg from "../portfolio/flyairways/fly-airways-devices.png";
import FlyAirwaysdesk from "../portfolio/flyairways/flyairways-desk.jpg";
import FlyAirwaysMob from "../portfolio/flyairways/flyairways-mob.jpg";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <MainHead
      title="airTRFX — Case Study | Priisma"
      description="How Priisma led product design for airTRFX at EveryMundo — a modular fare publishing platform that helped 20+ airlines increase revenue by an average of 20% per year."
      canonical="https://www.priisma.com/work/airtrfx"
      image="/assets/mesh-gradient.jpg"
    />
  </head>

  <body class="body-base">

    <header class="nav-floater">
      <Nav />
    </header>

    <main>

      <!-- ============================================================
           HERO
      ============================================================ -->
      <section class="section-space min-h-screen bg-linear-(--skyfly-gradient) text-paper">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl">
          <p class="eyebrow">Case Study</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-xs tracking-widest uppercase opacity-40">Product Design · UX · Web Development</p>
          <h1 class="mt-8 font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl max-w-4xl leading-[1.05]">
            Real-time fare pages for 20+ airlines. Built to scale.
          </h1>
          <p class="mt-6 max-w-lg text-base opacity-80">
            A modular fare publishing platform that turned airline search traffic into direct revenue.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-16">
            <figure>
              <Image
                src={FlyAirwaysImg}
                sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px"
                alt="airTRFX fare pages shown across desktop and mobile airline implementations"
                class="w-full border border-current/20"
                loading="eager"
              />
            </figure>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-12 text-center text-xl opacity-30" aria-hidden="true">↓</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================================
           CHALLENGE + APPROACH
      ============================================================ -->
      <section class="section-space bg-paper text-ink border-t border-current/10">
        <div class="grid items-start gap-12 mx-auto max-w-7xl md:grid-cols-2">
          <div>
            <p class="eyebrow mb-4">The Challenge</p>
            <p class="text-base">Airlines were leaving revenue on the table. Fare landing pages — the pages that live between a Google Flights search and an airline's booking flow — were generic, slow, and not conversion-optimized. EveryMundo's airTRFX platform set out to fix that: modular, real-time fare pages that could scale across 20+ airline brands without requiring custom builds for each one.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="eyebrow mb-4">The Approach</p>
            <p class="text-base">Product design at the platform level — not designing for one airline, but designing a system that could absorb the complexity of many without losing quality on any. That meant modular components, clear information hierarchy, and airline-specific customization baked into the product model from day one. Design workflows were built alongside five internal departments to cut delivery times by 40%.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================================
           01 — THE PLATFORM
      ============================================================ -->
      <section class="section-space bg-ink text-paper border-t border-current/10">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl">
          <p class="eyebrow mb-4">01 — Platform</p>
          <h2 class="section-header max-w-2xl">Designed to work for any airline, right out of the box.</h2>
          <div class="grid items-start gap-12 mt-10 md:grid-cols-2">
            <p class="text-base">airTRFX had to work for a wide range of airlines — from regional carriers to major alliances — each with different brand standards, routes, and performance needs. The design system was built to accommodate that range while maintaining a consistent, conversion-focused UX across all implementations. Over five major products and updates shipped across the engagement, each grounded in research and requirements from multiple stakeholders.</p>
            <div
              class="relative flex items-center justify-center w-full overflow-hidden border border-current/20 bg-white/5"
              style="aspect-ratio: 16/9;"
              role="img"
              aria-label="airTRFX platform — modular design system serving 20+ airlines"
            >
              <svg aria-hidden="true" class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full opacity-[0.04]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                <defs>
                  <pattern id="airtrfx-platform-grid" width="40" height="40" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
                    <path d="M 40 0 L 0 0 0 40" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1"/>
                  </pattern>
                </defs>
                <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#airtrfx-platform-grid)" />
              </svg>
              <p class="relative text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase opacity-30">Platform overview</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================================
           02 — DESKTOP + MOBILE
      ============================================================ -->
      <section class="section-space bg-mist text-ink border-t border-current/10">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl">
          <p class="eyebrow mb-4">02 — Execution</p>
          <h2 class="section-header max-w-2xl">Desktop and mobile — both first-class.</h2>
          <div class="grid items-start gap-12 mt-10 md:grid-cols-2">
            <p class="text-base">Fare pages have one primary conversion goal: get the traveler to click through to book. Every layout decision — information density, fare display, call-to-action placement — was made in service of that goal. Both desktop and mobile were designed as first-class experiences, with no afterthought implementations. The same modular approach that made the platform scalable also made it possible to optimize each breakpoint independently.</p>
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row">
              <figure class="flex-1">
                <Image
                  src={FlyAirwaysdesk}
                  sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"
                  alt="airTRFX desktop fare page implementation"
                  class="w-full border border-current/20"
                  loading="lazy"
                />
                <figcaption class="fig-caption">Desktop version</figcaption>
              </figure>
              <figure class="flex-1">
                <Image
                  src={FlyAirwaysMob}
                  sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"
                  alt="airTRFX mobile fare page implementation"
                  class="w-full border border-current/20"
                  loading="lazy"
                />
                <figcaption class="fig-caption">Mobile version</figcaption>
              </figure>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================================
           RESULT / CLOSE
      ============================================================ -->
      <section class="section-space bg-paper text-ink border-t border-current/10">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
          <h2 class="section-header">A platform that compounds.</h2>
          <p class="mt-8 text-base">Across 20+ airlines and alliances, airTRFX drove an average 20% revenue increase per year. Personalized module designs secured over $1.5M in new sales in a single quarter. The platform became the standard for how EveryMundo delivered fare publishing products — a design system that scaled without breaking. The kind of work that doesn't announce itself loudly, but keeps paying off quietly.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================================
           ROLE / CREDITS
      ============================================================ -->
      <section class="section-space bg-mist text-ink border-t border-current/10">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl">
          <h2 class="section-header mb-12">The work.</h2>
          <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-3">
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow mb-4">Design</p>
              <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm list-none">
                <li>Product design leadership</li>
                <li>Modular design system</li>
                <li>UX architecture</li>
                <li>Wireframing & prototyping</li>
                <li>Airline-specific customization</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow mb-4">Product</p>
              <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm list-none">
                <li>Fare landing pages</li>
                <li>Real-time fare display</li>
                <li>Search & discovery</li>
                <li>Conversion optimization</li>
                <li>Multi-airline platform</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="eyebrow mb-4">Development</p>
              <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm list-none">
                <li>HTML / CSS / JavaScript</li>
                <li>Responsive implementation</li>
                <li>Cross-airline delivery</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <dl class="mt-12 grid gap-4 text-sm md:grid-cols-3">
            <div>
              <dt class="eyebrow">Date</dt>
              <dd class="mt-1">2016–2018</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt class="eyebrow">Company</dt>
              <dd class="mt-1">EveryMundo</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt class="eyebrow">Role</dt>
              <dd class="mt-1">UI/UX Design + Web development</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================================
           CTA / NEXT
      ============================================================ -->
      <section class="section-space bg-ink text-paper border-t border-current/10">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-8 mx-auto max-w-7xl sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
          <div>
            <h2 class="section-header">Building something interesting?</h2>
            <p class="mt-2 text-base opacity-70">Let's talk.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col items-start gap-4 shrink-0 sm:flex-row sm:items-center">
            <a
              href="mailto:fede@priisma.com"
              class="font-medium text-ink bg-yellow rounded-none border-2 border-yellow hover:bg-yellow/90 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-yellow/50 px-6 py-3 inline-block"
            >
              Start a project →
            </a>
            <a
              href="/#work"
              class="inline-block text-sm font-medium underline opacity-60 hover:opacity-100 underline-offset-4 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-woodstock motion-safe:transition-opacity"
            >
              ← Back to work
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </main>

    <Footer />

  </body>
</html>
